    "text": "how are they even similar? a paper and a pen is a great tool for thought, but have nothing to do with end-user programming. and programming a Lego Mindstorm robot is done by an end-user, but has nothing to do with  being a tool for thought.\n\nUsing one to facilitate the other is an explicit choice, and should be a conscious and well-reasoned decision.",
